step_data.thought: Looking at the current state of the page, I can see that I'm already on the 'My Wish List' page. The URL in the RootWebArea confirms this: 'http://127.0.0.1:7770/wishlist/'. There are two places on the page that indicate the wish list status: one in the main content area and another further down the page. Both show the message 'You have no items in your wish list.' This means the user's wish list is currently empty. Since I've successfully navigated to the wish list page and can see its contents (which happens to be empty), I should inform the user about this.
